{
  "summary": "The article discusses how effective crisis leadership relies on leveraging technology to sustain stability and growth during challenging periods. By embracing automated communication tools and other tech solutions, organizations can better navigate crises characterized by volatility, uncertainty, complexity, ambiguity, and pandemics (VUCAP). These technologies enhance workflows, collaboration, planning, and AI-driven resilience, ultimately maintaining stakeholder trust and ensuring organizational adaptiveness.",
  "key_facts": [
    "Crisis leadership is more challenging than leadership during stable times.",
    "VUCAP stands for volatility, uncertainty, complexity, ambiguity, and pandemic, representing crisis conditions.",
    "Using automated communication tools is highlighted as a key strategy to handle VUCAP situations.",
    "Technology integration can improve workflows, collaboration, and strategic planning in times of crisis.",
    "Maintaining stakeholder trust and organizational stability are core goals of technological crisis leadership."
  ],
  "sources_represented": [
    "Forbes"
  ]
}

